                    <history>
                        <origin>

                            <origDate notBefore="1670" notAfter="1675"/>
<note>The frequent mention of king <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS10375Yohanne">John I</persName> and his queen <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS8276SablaWa">Sabla Wangel</persName>,
as well as of <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS6906Matthew">Matthew</persName>, patriarch of Alexandria, and <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS8870Sinoda">Sinodā</persName>, ʾabunā of Ethiopia on <locus target="#33v">f. 33v</locus> shows, that the manuscript was written between 1670 and 1675. </note>

                        </origin>
                        <provenance>The manuscript had very probably belonged to a church in the <placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LOC3577Gondar">Gondar</placeName> area,
                            from where it was taken by
                            <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS9430Tewodros">Tewodros</persName> and brought to <placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/INS0101MadhaneAlam">Madḫāne ʿĀlam</placeName>. It was then looted
                            by the British <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS7484Napier">Napier</persName> expedition in <date>1868</date>.</provenance>

                    </history>

